texts.label: section_header
texts.orig: Candidate is directed to read and comply with instructions hereunder before filling the Admission Form.
texts.text: Candidate is directed to read and comply with instructions hereunder before filling the Admission Form.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 1. The Admission Form found to be incomplete or containing incorrect entries will not be accepted/entertained and the candidate will be responsible for any sort of delay or loss.
texts.text: The Admission Form found to be incomplete or containing incorrect entries will not be accepted/entertained and the candidate will be responsible for any sort of delay or loss.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 2. Each candidate (Male/Female) must enclose three latest identical passport size Photographs (with sky blue background), duly attested, along-with the Admission Form. Two photographs must be pasted at the specified places on page 1 and other one be attached along-with the form (Name and Father's name must be mentioned on the back side of photographs).
texts.text: Each candidate (Male/Female) must enclose three latest identical passport size Photographs (with sky blue background), duly attested, along-with the Admission Form. Two photographs must be pasted at the specified places on page 1 and other one be attached along-with the form (Name and Father's name must be mentioned on the back side of photographs).

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 3. Admission form will be accepted according to the schedule notified by the University for each examination. The form with fee paid challan (together) must reach the Punjab University office within due date otherwise the form will be rejected.
texts.text: Admission form will be accepted according to the schedule notified by the University for each examination. The form with fee paid challan (together) must reach the Punjab University office within due date otherwise the form will be rejected.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 4. All the entries must be filled in with BLUE ballpoint. Don't use ink pen.
texts.text: All the entries must be filled in with BLUE ballpoint. Don't use ink pen.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 5. Clearly fill the examination in which you are appearing.
texts.text: Clearly fill the examination in which you are appearing.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 6. Fill your Name, Father's Name according to your Intermediate Certificate. In case of any discrepancy, the form will be rejected.
texts.text: Fill your Name, Father's Name according to your Intermediate Certificate. In case of any discrepancy, the form will be rejected.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 7. Fill the University Registration Number in the concerned column.
texts.text: Fill the University Registration Number in the concerned column.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 8. Name of Centre (City) where you want to appear in the examination must be filled in the concerned column.
texts.text: Name of Centre (City) where you want to appear in the examination must be filled in the concerned column.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 9. Fill the Name of Board from where you have passed the Intermediate examination with the passing year along-with roll number. Attach attested photocopy of Intermediate Certificate.
texts.text: Fill the Name of Board from where you have passed the Intermediate examination with the passing year along-with roll number. Attach attested photocopy of Intermediate Certificate.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 10. Deposit the required amount of fee in the Branches of Habib Bank registered with Punjab University. In case of any deficiency in the fee the form will not be entertained.
texts.text: Deposit the required amount of fee in the Branches of Habib Bank registered with Punjab University. In case of any deficiency in the fee the form will not be entertained.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 11. The examination will be held on the date/s to be notified in the date-sheet.
texts.text: The examination will be held on the date/s to be notified in the date-sheet.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 12. The candidates will be admitted to the Examination Hall on production of the Roll Number Slip. Candidates are advised not to appear in the Examination without genuine Roll Number Slips issued by the University. The candidates who will do so shall be proceeded against under the University Regulations.
texts.text: The candidates will be admitted to the Examination Hall on production of the Roll Number Slip. Candidates are advised not to appear in the Examination without genuine Roll Number Slips issued by the University. The candidates who will do so shall be proceeded against under the University Regulations.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 13. The admission form will be entertained only if the attested photocopies of registration card issued by the University is attached with the form alongwith other documents.
texts.text: The admission form will be entertained only if the attested photocopies of registration card issued by the University is attached with the form alongwith other documents.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 14. Unauthorized change of centre or subject is strictly prohibited. If any one changes his/her centre of Examination of his/her own, unfair means case shall be registered against such a candidate. Similarly no change of subject is allowed unless permitted by the University.
texts.text: Unauthorized change of centre or subject is strictly prohibited. If any one changes his/her centre of Examination of his/her own, unfair means case shall be registered against such a candidate. Similarly no change of subject is allowed unless permitted by the University.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 15. The order in which the candidates are seated will be forwarded to the Examiner. As and when a candidate be discovered to have copied from another he/she will be externed from the Examination as well as the candidate from whom he/she copied if there is reason to suppose that the copying was conceived at by the latter.
texts.text: The order in which the candidates are seated will be forwarded to the Examiner. As and when a candidate be discovered to have copied from another he/she will be externed from the Examination as well as the candidate from whom he/she copied if there is reason to suppose that the copying was conceived at by the latter.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 16. No candidate without special permission of the officer-in-charge shall leave his/her seat or the examination room till the end of the examination. No candidate shall speak without permission if it be necessary for the candidate to communicate with the Superintendent he/she shall stand up in his/her place and the officer-in-charge will see to his/her wants.
texts.text: No candidate without special permission of the officer-in-charge shall leave his/her seat or the examination room till the end of the examination. No candidate shall speak without permission if it be necessary for the candidate to communicate with the Superintendent he/she shall stand up in his/her place and the officer-in-charge will see to his/her wants.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 17. Before beginning his/her answer each candidate shall write on the title page of his/her answer book the following viz. Subject, the number of paper, and his/her Roll No. When the time allowed has expired the answer book must be delivered to the Superintendent, even though the candidate may not have answered any part of the paper.
texts.text: Before beginning his/her answer each candidate shall write on the title page of his/her answer book the following viz. Subject, the number of paper, and his/her Roll No. When the time allowed has expired the answer book must be delivered to the Superintendent, even though the candidate may not have answered any part of the paper.

texts.label: list_item
texts.orig: 18. No candidate shall give any mark of identification including his/her Roll No. Name, of School/college or Centre of examination in his/her answer book except at specified place. Such candidates shall be proceeded against under the University Regulations.
texts.text: No candidate shall give any mark of identification including his/her Roll No. Name, of School/college or Centre of examination in his/her answer book except at specified place. Such candidates shall be proceeded against under the University Regulations.

texts.label: section_header
texts.orig: 19. Money orders, Postal orders, Bank Drafts & Cheques shall not be accepted
texts.text: 19. Money orders, Postal orders, Bank Drafts & Cheques shall not be accepted
